external_knowledge:
- The status of '1' in the 'transactions' table refers to completed transactions;
- The transaction type 'sale' indicates a purchase;
- Average amount spent > 50 represents a moderate to high spending threshold.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(fk_customer_reward) AS total_rewards_earned
FROM customer_rewards
WHERE fk_customer = 12345;

SELECT DISTINCT c.customer_name
FROM customers c
JOIN customer_rewards cr ON c.fk_customer = cr.fk_customer;
